Sri Lanka to Allow China Yuan Use in International Transactions

-- B y   K e n   M c C a l l u m
-- 
2011-06-29T23:57:51Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-06-29/sri-lanka-to-allow-china-yuan-use-in-international-transactions.html
Sri Lanka ’s central bank said it
will allow China’s currency to be used in international
transactions at authorized banks.  Permitting the use of the yuan in banking transactions will
facilitate trade and investment between the two countries, the
 Central Bank of Sri Lanka  said in a statement released on its
website yesterday.  The central bank also allows international banking
transactions in 13 other foreign currencies including the U.S.
dollar, euro and yen, according to the statement.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Ken McCallum in Tokyo at 
